1
00:00:21,666 --> 00:00:25,125
[INOUE]
Kobayashi! Hey! Dammit.

2
00:00:25,208 --> 00:00:29,250
How many times have I told
you not to act on your own?

3
00:00:29,333 --> 00:00:30,458
[gasps]

4
00:00:36,583 --> 00:00:37,791
[gasps]

5
00:00:43,666 --> 00:00:45,291
[INOUE]
Stop and think!

6
00:00:46,625 --> 00:00:48,708
[INOUE]
Hanasaki is probably up there.

7
00:00:48,791 --> 00:00:50,958
The way things are looking,
Twenty-Faces has complete

8
00:00:51,041 --> 00:00:53,416
control over the security
system. We need a pl--

9
00:00:56,875 --> 00:00:58,208
[KATSUTA grunts]

10
00:00:59,125 --> 00:01:00,500
[gasps]

11
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:12,708
[KENSUKE grunts]

12
00:01:12,791 --> 00:01:16,791
Who said you could move?
Next time, you'll get a bullet.

13
00:01:16,875 --> 00:01:19,625
[KENSUKE grunts]

14
00:01:19,708 --> 00:01:21,458
[TWENTY-FACES]
Ha.

15
00:01:21,541 --> 00:01:22,666
[AKECHI grunts]

16
00:01:22,750 --> 00:01:24,875
[TWENTY-FACES]
All the actors are in place.

17
00:01:36,041 --> 00:01:41,000
♪

18
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:24,041
[NORO grunts]

19
00:03:24,125 --> 00:03:25,500
[NORO]
Dammit!

20
00:03:25,583 --> 00:03:26,625
[OHTOMO]
Throwing a hissy fit

21
00:03:26,708 --> 00:03:29,333
isn't gonna make the
jamming go away.

22
00:03:29,416 --> 00:03:30,750
[NORO groans]

23
00:03:30,833 --> 00:03:34,166
You can mash the keys all day.
It won't work. Sorry.

24
00:03:34,250 --> 00:03:38,250
The robots' operating systems
are out of reach, for now.

25
00:03:38,333 --> 00:03:41,458
[NORO]
Hm? For now? What?

26
00:03:41,541 --> 00:03:42,541
[OHTOMO]
Come on, Noro.

27
00:03:42,625 --> 00:03:44,500
I thought you were
smarter than this.

28
00:03:44,583 --> 00:03:45,916
[NORO growls]

29
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:50,833
There's work to be done.
I don't have time to babysit.

30
00:03:50,916 --> 00:03:56,458
Did... you just... call me..
I am not a baby!

31
00:03:56,541 --> 00:04:01,000
You... You... stupid jerk face!

32
00:04:09,166 --> 00:04:11,291
[MALE STAFF A]
Someone!

33
00:04:11,375 --> 00:04:13,500
Help us!

34
00:04:13,583 --> 00:04:16,875
[MALL STAFF chatter]

35
00:04:16,958 --> 00:04:18,791
More hostages.

36
00:04:23,125 --> 00:04:26,000
[gasps]
How many?

37
00:04:26,083 --> 00:04:27,625
[KATSUTA]
Around twenty.

38
00:04:27,708 --> 00:04:29,583
And three security bots.

39
00:04:29,666 --> 00:04:31,500
[KATSUTA]
Think we can?

40
00:04:31,583 --> 00:04:33,583
Do you think we
have a choice?

41
00:04:42,291 --> 00:04:44,458
[NAKAMURA]
I'm telling you...

42
00:04:44,541 --> 00:04:46,458
...nothing is going
on at the complex!

43
00:04:46,541 --> 00:04:49,541
Le Waqua's security system says
everything is in the green.

44
00:04:49,625 --> 00:04:53,458
[NORO] And I'm telling you
it's a total mess in there!

45
00:04:53,541 --> 00:04:55,083
[NAKAMURA]
The word of a child isn't enough

46
00:04:55,166 --> 00:04:56,833
to justify police action!

47
00:04:56,916 --> 00:04:59,166
If something blew up,
it'd be a different story.

48
00:04:59,250 --> 00:05:01,291
[MIYANISHI] Cool it.
Don't take your anger out on her

49
00:05:01,375 --> 00:05:02,625
just cause you
miss your boyfriend.

50
00:05:02,708 --> 00:05:04,833
[NAKAMURA]
You wanna die?

51
00:05:04,916 --> 00:05:07,208
[growls]

52
00:05:07,291 --> 00:05:09,041
[phone buzzes]

53
00:05:09,125 --> 00:05:14,083
[YOSHIO pants]

54
00:05:23,458 --> 00:05:27,541
[YOSHIO]
Where are you? Hey!

55
00:05:27,625 --> 00:05:29,625
You're such a pain
in the ass, man.

56
00:05:29,708 --> 00:05:32,083
Why am I doing this for you?

57
00:05:34,083 --> 00:05:35,541
[YOSHIO]
Quit ignoring me!

58
00:05:36,791 --> 00:05:39,750
Hey! Hanasaki!

59
00:05:41,333 --> 00:05:42,375
[YOSHIO gasps]

60
00:05:55,416 --> 00:05:56,625
[gasps]

61
00:06:23,375 --> 00:06:24,750
[KATSUTA grunts]

62
00:06:28,333 --> 00:06:29,500
[INOUE]
Got you!

63
00:06:32,166 --> 00:06:33,166
[KATSUTA grunts]

64
00:06:37,375 --> 00:06:40,291
Now's your chance!
Get out of here!

65
00:06:40,375 --> 00:06:42,583
[MALL STAFF gasp]

66
00:06:44,125 --> 00:06:47,458
[TWENTY-FACES chuckles]

67
00:06:47,541 --> 00:06:51,083
[TWENTY-FACES] I expected no
less from your right-hand man.

68
00:06:51,166 --> 00:06:53,375
Impressive.

69
00:06:53,458 --> 00:06:54,791
[AKECHI]
What about me?

70
00:06:54,875 --> 00:06:55,791
[TWENTY-FACES]
Hm.

71
00:06:55,875 --> 00:06:58,458
[AKECHI]
I'm the one you're after.

72
00:06:58,541 --> 00:07:00,875
Let's get this
over with already.

73
00:07:04,541 --> 00:07:09,416
[TWENTY-FACES] Hm. Not yet.
We have another visitor.

74
00:07:12,958 --> 00:07:17,041
[KENSUKE]
Kobayashi. You came, too?

75
00:07:18,625 --> 00:07:23,125
[TWENTY-FACES] Hello.
It's good to see you again.

76
00:07:23,208 --> 00:07:26,875
Well, Kensuke? He has come
all this way to save you.

77
00:07:26,958 --> 00:07:28,125
You could say something.

78
00:07:28,208 --> 00:07:29,416
[YOSHIO]
Stop it!

79
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:31,250
[TWENTY-FACES]
Mm.

80
00:07:31,333 --> 00:07:34,291
Stop changing. I can't keep up!

81
00:07:34,375 --> 00:07:35,000
[KENSUKE]
Huh?

82
00:07:35,083 --> 00:07:40,041
[YOSHIO pants]

83
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:46,083
[YOSHIO] You laugh...
then get mad or cry.

84
00:07:46,166 --> 00:07:50,083
[YOSHIO pants]
Pull yourself together!

85
00:07:52,666 --> 00:07:53,833
And as for you...

86
00:07:53,916 --> 00:07:54,708
[AKECHI]
Hm?

87
00:07:54,791 --> 00:07:56,625
You're too damn weak.

88
00:07:56,708 --> 00:07:59,875
[AKECHI]
Hmph. Whatever.

89
00:07:59,958 --> 00:08:02,708
[YOSHIO] I'll say it once.
If you're okay with looking like

90
00:08:02,791 --> 00:08:04,833
such a lame-ass,
then you should just...

91
00:08:04,916 --> 00:08:07,083
"Just die already."

92
00:08:09,916 --> 00:08:11,333
[YOSHIO grunts]

93
00:08:11,416 --> 00:08:13,791
[TWENTY-FACES]
Right?

94
00:08:13,875 --> 00:08:15,666
Don't lie.

95
00:08:15,750 --> 00:08:19,583
We both know his death is
the last thing you want.

96
00:08:19,666 --> 00:08:22,333
So then--

97
00:08:22,416 --> 00:08:24,333
How about Akechi?

98
00:08:26,166 --> 00:08:28,166
Or your other friends?

99
00:08:33,333 --> 00:08:35,000
[KENSUKE]
Please, stop.

100
00:08:35,083 --> 00:08:39,125
[TWENTY-FACES chuckles]
You can't make me.

101
00:08:39,208 --> 00:08:41,208
You won't even try.

102
00:08:42,666 --> 00:08:43,875
[TWENTY-FACES chuckles]

103
00:08:43,958 --> 00:08:47,583
Think they're weak?
You're exactly like them.

104
00:08:47,666 --> 00:08:49,250
Say what?

105
00:08:49,333 --> 00:08:52,250
[TWENTY-FACES] That's the price
of being part of a group.

106
00:08:52,333 --> 00:08:53,500
Understand?

107
00:08:53,583 --> 00:08:56,250
I couldn't understand
someone like you.

108
00:08:56,333 --> 00:08:59,125
[TWENTY-FACES chuckles]
Then what are you going to do?

109
00:08:59,208 --> 00:09:00,083
[YOSHIO gasps]

110
00:09:00,166 --> 00:09:02,708
Well. Hanasaki?

111
00:09:02,791 --> 00:09:03,875
[gasps]

112
00:09:03,958 --> 00:09:06,875
[TWENTY-FACES]
What do... you want to do?

113
00:09:06,958 --> 00:09:08,416
[KENSUKE gasps]

114
00:09:11,083 --> 00:09:15,166
Silence is your answer?
How disappointing.

115
00:09:15,250 --> 00:09:18,000
--[alarm blares]
--[KENSUKE gasps]

116
00:09:18,083 --> 00:09:19,208
[YOSHIO]
No!

117
00:09:24,291 --> 00:09:26,708
[SECURITY ROBOT A]
Boing. Boing. Boing.

118
00:09:26,791 --> 00:09:27,875
[INOUE, KATSUTA gasp]

119
00:09:27,958 --> 00:09:32,541
[SECURITY ROBOTS]
Boing. Boing. Boing...

120
00:09:33,916 --> 00:09:34,458
[SECURITY ROBOTS]
Pippo!

121
00:09:34,541 --> 00:09:37,250
Nicely done, Noro.

122
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:42,000
[NORO] Sadly, I can't
take credit for this.

123
00:09:42,083 --> 00:09:43,833
I was useless without him.

124
00:09:43,916 --> 00:09:45,208
[INOUE]
Huh?

125
00:09:45,291 --> 00:09:51,416
Today's MVP goes to...
Ohtomo and his crazy drones!

126
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:53,541
Canceling a signal
jam's a piece of cake.

127
00:09:53,625 --> 00:09:55,291
You can thank me later.

128
00:09:55,375 --> 00:09:58,375
[SECURITY ROBOTS]
Boing. Boing. Boing.

129
00:09:58,458 --> 00:10:02,333
And now... to get the
police's attention! Boom!

130
00:10:09,625 --> 00:10:10,708
[footsteps]

131
00:10:10,791 --> 00:10:11,916
[AKECHI grunts]

132
00:10:16,208 --> 00:10:19,375
It's over. Come quietly.

133
00:10:19,458 --> 00:10:23,166
[TWENTY-FACES chuckles]
I'll pass.

134
00:10:23,250 --> 00:10:24,333
[TWENTY-FACES]
I'll pass.

135
00:10:24,416 --> 00:10:27,625
This is only the beginning,
dear Akechi.

136
00:10:29,125 --> 00:10:30,333
[INOUE, KATSUTA gasp]

137
00:10:36,916 --> 00:10:38,333
[gasps]

138
00:10:42,083 --> 00:10:44,750
Late as usual.
Should have known.

139
00:10:44,833 --> 00:10:49,166
[police sirens blaring]

140
00:10:49,250 --> 00:10:51,791
[YUMEKO gasps]
Wait, isn't that?

141
00:11:02,791 --> 00:11:05,416
[NORO]
What? Why's the signal gone?

142
00:11:05,500 --> 00:11:07,375
[OHTOMO]
That's bizarre.

143
00:11:08,125 --> 00:11:10,125
I put jamming cancelers
in all of them.

144
00:11:10,208 --> 00:11:13,458
It should have worked.
This is exactly why I hate

145
00:11:13,541 --> 00:11:16,541
getting involved with
that masked bastard.

146
00:11:20,250 --> 00:11:21,708
How'd you do it?

147
00:11:24,083 --> 00:11:25,500
Those poor people.

148
00:11:25,583 --> 00:11:28,750
You used some weird power again
to brainwash them, right?

149
00:11:28,833 --> 00:11:30,791
[TWENTY-FACES]
"Some weird power?"

150
00:11:30,875 --> 00:11:35,041
Heh. It's simply
a gift I gave them.

151
00:11:35,125 --> 00:11:37,125
Nothing more or less.

152
00:11:37,208 --> 00:11:39,166
[grunts]

153
00:11:39,250 --> 00:11:42,125
[AKECHI]
What did you tell them?

154
00:11:42,208 --> 00:11:44,000
[TWENTY-FACES] I said
"You are the ones who will

155
00:11:44,083 --> 00:11:48,083
protect this place. If the
security robots shut down,

156
00:11:48,166 --> 00:11:50,125
you are to fight off
any intruders, no-- "

157
00:11:50,208 --> 00:11:52,625
What are you guys talking about?
This is stupid.

158
00:11:52,708 --> 00:11:54,708
[TWENTY-FACES] I hope the
police don't try to waltz in

159
00:11:54,791 --> 00:11:58,666
to my new playground. If they
happen to bump into each other--

160
00:11:58,750 --> 00:12:01,000
[YOSHIO]
Let's take Hanasaki and go!

161
00:12:01,083 --> 00:12:04,375
[TWENTY-FACES] I wonder what
will happen. Hm, hm, hm.

162
00:12:04,458 --> 00:12:05,750
Don't ignore me!

163
00:12:05,833 --> 00:12:09,375
[AKECHI] Kobayashi! Be quiet
for a minute, would you?

164
00:12:09,458 --> 00:12:11,000
[YOSHIO gasps]

165
00:12:11,083 --> 00:12:16,916
Now I could stop them,
of course. It's not too late.

166
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:19,291
However.

167
00:12:19,375 --> 00:12:22,541
I'll need something
from you. Kill him.

168
00:12:22,625 --> 00:12:24,416
[gasps]

169
00:12:24,500 --> 00:12:27,416
Do that, and I'll call
them off immediately.

170
00:12:27,500 --> 00:12:28,958
Yeah, right.

171
00:12:29,041 --> 00:12:33,291
Sacrificing just one life will
prevent the loss of dozens.

172
00:12:33,375 --> 00:12:35,541
If you ask me, that's a bargain.

173
00:12:35,625 --> 00:12:37,041
That's not happening.

174
00:12:37,125 --> 00:12:40,000
You might as well.

175
00:12:40,083 --> 00:12:43,416
The Hanasaki you knew
is long gone, my dear.

176
00:12:43,500 --> 00:12:45,500
[AKECHI gasps]

177
00:12:45,583 --> 00:12:49,416
[AKECHI]
Bastard. You got to him, too?

178
00:12:49,500 --> 00:12:52,125
Which one would be more
thrilling for you?

179
00:12:52,208 --> 00:12:57,125
That I got to him, or not?
I think we both know the answer.

180
00:12:57,208 --> 00:12:58,708
[AKECHI gasps]

181
00:12:58,791 --> 00:13:00,125
[TWENTY-FACES]
Poor thing.

182
00:13:00,208 --> 00:13:04,125
Can you continue to love him,
as you did before?

183
00:13:04,208 --> 00:13:05,875
Stop talking.

184
00:13:09,083 --> 00:13:12,833
Now. What's your answer?

185
00:13:12,916 --> 00:13:14,416
That's enough!

186
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:23,125
Pull the trigger.
All of this... is my fault.

187
00:13:23,208 --> 00:13:26,583
Do it. Kill me now!

188
00:13:26,666 --> 00:13:27,541
[AKECHI gasps]

189
00:13:27,625 --> 00:13:31,541
[KENSUKE]
Please, boss!

190
00:13:31,625 --> 00:13:34,000
I deserve to die!

191
00:13:34,083 --> 00:13:39,833
I can't let... you suffer.
Come on! Do it!

192
00:13:39,916 --> 00:13:41,208
[KENSUKE grunts]

193
00:13:47,166 --> 00:13:50,833
[TWENTY-FACES] Oh, and...
We can't forget your father.

194
00:13:50,916 --> 00:13:52,333
[KENSUKE]
Huh?

195
00:13:55,166 --> 00:13:56,416
[KENSUKE gasps]

196
00:13:56,500 --> 00:13:59,416
Remember Isuzu, the woman
Haruhiko adored so much?

197
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:00,958
Your father sure does.

198
00:14:01,041 --> 00:14:03,208
[AKECHI]
Hanasaki! Don't listen!

199
00:14:03,291 --> 00:14:04,833
[TWENTY-FACES] Whether because
he was threatened,

200
00:14:04,916 --> 00:14:08,000
or simply loved his adopted son.

201
00:14:08,083 --> 00:14:10,916
Daddy dearest sent Ms. Isuzu
huge amounts of money

202
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:14,208
so your wayward brother would
be supported. Isn't that sweet?

203
00:14:14,291 --> 00:14:15,875
[KENSUKE]
You're lying!

204
00:14:18,666 --> 00:14:22,625
Perhaps he did it simply out
of concern for his company,

205
00:14:22,708 --> 00:14:27,083
or because he truly cares
about Haruhiko's well-being.

206
00:14:27,166 --> 00:14:30,125
[KENSUKE sobs]

207
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:35,208
You don't know how
your father feels.

208
00:14:35,291 --> 00:14:36,375
[AKECHI]
Faces!

209
00:14:36,458 --> 00:14:40,333
[TWENTY-FACES chuckles]
Yet you did this.

210
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:43,250
[AKECHI]
Damn you.

211
00:14:43,333 --> 00:14:46,666
[KENSUKE sobs]
No more.

212
00:14:46,750 --> 00:14:52,208
I've had enough. I did it.
It's all my fault.

213
00:14:52,291 --> 00:14:54,458
[AKECHI]
Hanasaki!

214
00:14:54,541 --> 00:14:59,125
[KENSUKE] Please, just kill me.
I want to die so badly.

215
00:15:00,750 --> 00:15:05,833
That's my line.
Don't start copying me.

216
00:15:05,916 --> 00:15:07,041
[KENSUKE gasps]

217
00:15:08,416 --> 00:15:10,000
Understand?

218
00:15:11,791 --> 00:15:16,291
Don't you dare. I'm the one
who's supposed to die. Not you!

219
00:15:16,375 --> 00:15:17,958
[exhales]

220
00:15:20,791 --> 00:15:23,416
[grunts]

221
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:26,791
There it is. Very nice.

222
00:15:26,875 --> 00:15:30,583
I waited all this time for you
to grow fond of these boys.

223
00:15:30,666 --> 00:15:34,083
Now, after finally getting to
see that look on your face.

224
00:15:34,166 --> 00:15:36,375
I can say it was worth it.

225
00:15:38,166 --> 00:15:39,541
[TWENTY-FACES] Things are
about to get interesting.

226
00:15:39,625 --> 00:15:42,416
[YOSHIO]
Hey, old man. Shut up!

227
00:15:43,791 --> 00:15:48,291
[YOSHIO] What's the plan?
Tell me what to do! Please!

228
00:15:48,375 --> 00:15:50,375
Come on, why are just
you standing there?

229
00:15:50,458 --> 00:15:51,583
[KENSUKE]
Just give it up.

230
00:15:51,666 --> 00:15:52,791
[YOSHIO gasps]

231
00:15:56,750 --> 00:15:58,166
[gasps]

232
00:16:02,208 --> 00:16:04,791
Hansaki, no!

233
00:16:04,875 --> 00:16:08,750
[KENSUKE] Don't do anything,
Kobayashi. Stay put.

234
00:16:12,833 --> 00:16:14,250
[grunts]

235
00:16:16,416 --> 00:16:21,833
I'll end it. It's the
only way I can atone.

236
00:16:21,916 --> 00:16:25,083
[laughs]
You guys.

237
00:16:31,041 --> 00:16:33,000
I'm sorry.

238
00:16:35,125 --> 00:16:36,125
[AKECHI grunts]

239
00:16:45,833 --> 00:16:48,750
[grunts]
Hanasaki!

240
00:16:48,833 --> 00:16:50,875
[gasps]

241
00:16:53,916 --> 00:16:54,916
[gasps]

242
00:17:21,208 --> 00:17:23,541
[gasps]

243
00:17:34,458 --> 00:17:35,708
[TWENTY-FACES]
Wow.

244
00:17:37,875 --> 00:17:39,041
[TWENTY-FACES]
Hm.

245
00:17:42,500 --> 00:17:44,291
[chuckles]

246
00:17:44,375 --> 00:17:48,583
[KENSUKE pants]

247
00:17:54,708 --> 00:17:55,791
[gasps]

248
00:17:58,000 --> 00:17:59,375
[gasps]

249
00:17:59,458 --> 00:18:00,500
[INOUE gasps]

250
00:18:00,583 --> 00:18:02,000
I guess it's over.

251
00:18:02,083 --> 00:18:04,250
[INOUE]
Hm Fine by me.

252
00:18:10,708 --> 00:18:14,791
[KENSUKE groans]
Kobayashi.

253
00:18:27,750 --> 00:18:29,125
[TWENTY-FACES]
Too bad.

254
00:18:29,208 --> 00:18:32,083
[AKECHI]
That's... enough.

255
00:18:34,583 --> 00:18:40,041
[AKECHI grunts]
Let's just... end... it.

256
00:18:41,166 --> 00:18:42,875
[TWENTY-FACES]
It won't end.

257
00:18:47,916 --> 00:18:50,166
[TWENTY-FACES]
I love you too much for that.

258
00:18:52,250 --> 00:18:56,125
[TWENTY-FACES] That's also
why I won't forgive you.

259
00:19:14,375 --> 00:19:15,916
[TWENTY-FACES]
Thrilling, isn't it?

260
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:17,625
[YOSHIO]
Hm?

261
00:19:20,208 --> 00:19:21,875
[TWENTY-FACES]
That gift of yours.

262
00:19:21,958 --> 00:19:24,583
It's far greater than mine.

263
00:19:24,666 --> 00:19:27,625
[YOSHIO]
Gift? Tsk.

264
00:19:27,708 --> 00:19:30,375
[TWENTY-FACES]
I'm a bit... jealous.

265
00:19:30,458 --> 00:19:31,416
[police sirens]

266
00:19:31,500 --> 00:19:33,125
[YOSHIO]
Huh?

267
00:19:33,208 --> 00:19:35,500
[TWENTY-FACES]
Let's play again soon.

268
00:19:43,500 --> 00:19:44,666
[YOSHIO sighs]
Tsk.

269
00:19:51,416 --> 00:19:53,750
[AKECHI grunts]

270
00:19:53,833 --> 00:19:55,416
[NAKAMURA]
Wakey, wakey.

271
00:20:00,083 --> 00:20:03,583
[AKECHI] Hey, Nao.
Can you give me a light?

272
00:20:03,666 --> 00:20:04,958
[NAKAMURA]
You did good.

273
00:20:05,041 --> 00:20:06,833
[AKECHI grunts]

274
00:20:06,916 --> 00:20:08,916
With Twenty-Faces, I mean.

275
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:10,166
[AKECHI gasps]

276
00:20:11,541 --> 00:20:13,000
[MIYANISHI] He should be
watched around the clock.

277
00:20:13,083 --> 00:20:14,916
Don't take your eyes off him.

278
00:20:18,541 --> 00:20:20,416
Thank goodness.

279
00:20:20,500 --> 00:20:23,375
With him gone, we can
finally clean up his messes.

280
00:20:23,458 --> 00:20:26,833
Of course, I'll be expecting
your assistance with that.

281
00:20:35,625 --> 00:20:36,791
[KENSUKE gasps]

282
00:20:41,916 --> 00:20:44,041
Remain on stand-by, for now.

283
00:20:50,916 --> 00:20:52,250
[KENSUKE]
Kobayashi!

284
00:20:53,625 --> 00:20:57,208
[KENSUKE grunts]

285
00:20:57,291 --> 00:20:59,625
[KENSUKE]
About all that.

286
00:20:59,708 --> 00:21:02,333
[YOSHIO] Whatever, just...
keep your promise.

287
00:21:02,416 --> 00:21:04,041
[KENSUKE]
Huh?

288
00:21:04,125 --> 00:21:08,541
I'm waiting. Find a
way to kill me soon.

289
00:21:08,625 --> 00:21:10,041
[gasps]

290
00:21:15,666 --> 00:21:18,833
[KENSUKE sobs]

291
00:21:18,916 --> 00:21:20,458
[KENSUKE]
Forgive me.

292
00:21:24,208 --> 00:21:27,916
[KENSUKE]
I'm so sorry. I am.

293
00:21:36,541 --> 00:21:40,125
[yawns]

294
00:21:47,458 --> 00:21:52,416
♪

295
00:23:38,208 --> 00:23:41,458
[TWENTY-FACES] "Wild Dance
of the Luminous Man."

